name.text: Using a calculator to find the reciprocal of a number

questiontext.text:
Use a calculator to find the reciprocal of each number. Leave your answers to 4 decimal places.

  1. {@a@} [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]

  2. {@b@} [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]

[[feedback:prt1]] [[feedback:prt2]]

generalfeedback.text:
Worked Solution

To find reciprocal of \({@a@}\) and \({@b@}\) using a calculator:

  1. Enter the number into the calculator
  2. Press the reciprocal button x^(-1) on the calculator
  3. Read the displayed result.
  1. Therefore, the reciprocal of \({@a@}\) is \(({@ta@}\)
    \( = {@ta1@} \) when rounded off.
  2. The reciprocal of \({@b@}\) is \({@b_ta@}\) .
    \(= {@ta2@} \)

prtcorrect.text: Correct answer, well done.

prtpartiallycorrect.text: Your answer is partially correct.

prtincorrect.text: Incorrect answer.

truefeedback.text: You have mistaken the reciprocal for the additive inverse (negative) of the number.
